IKR34ETYUSs.title: Head YouTek Graphene Radical S | Racquet Review | Tennis Express
IKR34ETYUSs.description:
http://www.tennisexpress.com/head-YouTek-Graphene-Radical-S-Tennis-Racquet-35587

Head's popular Radical series gets a new update that brings their Graphene technology to the lineup. Introduced last year on the Speed and Instinct lines, this new frame technology is now incorporated into the Radical series. Graphene, the world's strongest and lightest material, has allowed Head to redistribute the frame's weight for optimal handling and increased power. Head aims to open the Radical experience to an even broader range of players with the introduction of the Head Youtek Graphene Radical S. This frame is centered around offering a bit more forgiveness than the Pro and MP, allowing more players to feel the unique tour playing characteristics of the Radical line. Its 100 square inch head size allows it a larger sweet spot and forgiving string bed while still being capable of providing plenty of power. Although it 9.9oz (unstrung) weight may seem light, Graphene allows the weight to be redistributed in a manner that imparts a solid and stable feel on contact. The racquet also retains a head light balance, giving it a light and fast feel that players of a wide range of abilities will enjoy. Head also incorporates its new Dynamic 16/19 string pattern. This pattern puts eight main strings in the heart of the racquet, giving it an optimal blend of tight pattern control and open pattern spin generation and forgiveness. Intermediate players and stronger players seeking a lighter frame will enjoy the Graphene Radical S for its comfortable, easy feel and quality blend of power, control and forgiveness.

Head size: 102, Length: 27", Weight: 10.4 oz strung, String pattern: 16 x 19

zj-ZD8uET9c.title: Is EPS Foam (Aka Styrofoam) Recyclable? Expanded Polystyrene Foam
zj-ZD8uET9c.description:
http://www.EPSFoamPro.com

Yes, Expanded Polystyrene (EPS) is recyclable! With all of the regulations in the US and around the world, EPS foam is being recycled more than ever. What people dont realize is that EPS is 100% recyclable, and that manufacturers have 0% waste. Scrap foam is grinded up and molded back into scrap blocks, and eventually the rest of the recycled foam is sold to companies that make trash bags.
